    {
      "id": "browser-bar-reader",
      "type": "port",
      "label": "Browser Bar Reader",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -520,
        "y": -1440
      },
      "width": 320,
      "height": 210,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        },
        "view": {
          "intent": "node",
          "payload": "node.web.detail"
        },
        "renderShape": {
          "kind": "markdown"
        },
        "markdown": "# The Browser Bar\n---\n\nThis lesson explains how to read the browser bar, how to use its controls to stay oriented, and how to tell whether you are looking at a GitHub-backed graph or a local one."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-intro",
      "type": "tutorial-title",
      "label": "Lesson Hero",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -180,
        "y": -1100
      },
      "width": 620,
      "height": 260,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "The Browser Bar",
        "subtitle": "Learn what the address field, navigation controls, bookmarks, refresh, and zoom indicator are telling you before you edit or trust what you see.",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-title",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-title.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-title.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-title",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-title.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-title",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-address-note",
      "type": "tutorial-concept",
      "label": "Address Field",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -760,
        "y": -520
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Read The Address First",
        "body": "The large address field tells you what graph you are actually in. A `github://...` address means you are reading a GitHub-backed artifact path. A local or untitled address means the save and trust story is different.",
        "tag": "Concept",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-concept",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-concept",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-concept",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-controls-note",
      "type": "tutorial-concept",
      "label": "Controls + Indicator",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": -300,
        "y": -520
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Use The Controls To Stay Oriented",
        "body": "Back, forward, home, refresh, bookmarks, and the position or zoom indicator are trust tools, not decoration. They help you recover your place, confirm where you are, and reset your view when the graph gets large.",
        "tag": "Concept",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-concept",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-concept",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-concept",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-hosting-note",
      "type": "tutorial-concept",
      "label": "GitHub + Hosting",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 160,
        "y": -520
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "GitHub Context Is Nearby",
        "body": "The browser bar can tell you that a graph is GitHub-backed, but it does not by itself explain repository hosting, commit flow, or public delivery. Keep that related topic nearby without mixing every GitHub concern into this lesson.",
        "tag": "Concept",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-concept",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-concept",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-concept.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-concept",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-example",
      "type": "tutorial-example",
      "label": "Examples",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 640,
        "y": -520
      },
      "width": 400,
      "height": 240,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Examples",
        "body": "Use the nearby sample note as a quick readout of what the browser bar is telling you. The lesson is intentionally small: read the address, trust the controls, and follow the related GitHub material only when you need the next layer.",
        "cta": "Inspect the sample",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-example",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-example.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-example.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-example",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-example.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-example",
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-sample-note",
      "type": "markdown",
      "label": "Browser Bar Checklist",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 640,
        "y": -120
      },
      "width": 430,
      "height": 300,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "identity": {
          "graphId": "tutorial-interface-browser-bar"
        },
        "markdown": "## Quick browser-bar checklist\n\nBefore you edit a graph, ask:\n\n- What address am I actually on?\n- Is this `github://`, local, or temporary?\n- Do I trust back, home, and refresh to get me out again?\n- What is the zoom or position indicator telling me?\n- Do I need the GitHub lesson, or just this interface lesson?\n\nThe browser bar is one of Twilite's main trust surfaces."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "browser-bar-challenge",
      "type": "tutorial-challenge",
      "label": "Challenge",
      "root": false,
      "position": {
        "x": 1140,
        "y": -120
      },
      "width": 360,
      "height": 220,
      "visible": true,
      "showLabel": true,
      "data": {
        "title": "Challenge",
        "body": "1. Open a graph with a `github://` address.\n2. Say what the address is telling you about where the graph lives.\n3. Use refresh, home, or back deliberately instead of guessing.\n4. Reset the view if the zoom indicator says you are far from `1x`.\n5. Explain when you would leave this lesson and open the GitHub material.",
        "difficulty": "starter",
        "_classBinding": {
          "key": "tutorial-challenge",
          "sourceRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-challenge.node-class.node",
          "ref": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-challenge.node-class.node"
        },
        "_bridge": {
          "classKey": "tutorial-challenge",
          "classRef": "github://twilite-zone/public/tutorial/basic-primitives/tutorial-challenge.node-class.node"
        },
        "definitionKey": "tutorial-challenge",
